I first came across this when trying to use a Scale9Sprite as the stencil for ClippingNode. On mobile devices ClippingNode recursively calls setGLProgram on it's stencil renderer and it's children, however Scale9Sprite's subsprites are stored as protected children and are not effected by this process.

My current solution is to implement setGLProgram for Scale9Sprite as such:

void Scale9Sprite::setGLProgram(GLProgram *glprogram)
{
    Node::setGLProgram(glprogram);
    if(_scale9Image)
    {
        _scale9Image->setGLProgram(glprogram);
    }
    if(_scale9Enabled)
    {
        for( const auto &child: _protectedChildren )
        {
            child->setGLProgram(glprogram);
        }
    }
}
